cs.HC, cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.CY, cs.SI 

This paper focuses on user interaction with websites, specifically exploring the use of out-of-turn interaction. Therefore, the most likely category is Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC). Information Retrieval (cs.IR) is also relevant as the study involves information-finding tasks. Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) could also be a relevant category as the user interface accepts input via voice or text. Cybersecurity (cs.CY) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) are less likely but still possible categories as the study involves a congressional website and user behavior.
